The Zamfara State government has uncovered abandoned hospital equipment supplied about six years ago. The chairman of the state’s Task Force Committee on Coronavirus, Nasiru Magarya, who led the state governor, Bello Matawalle to the abandoned containers, said that his team uncovered the containers in the hospital premises. According to him, the hospitals equipment were procured by the immediate past administration but refused to distribute to the hospitals. “Hospital equipment included electrically controlled beds, chairs, mattresses and other basic equipment,” he added. He expressed shock over how the past government misused the equipment at a time when the hospital required them and urged the management to put them to effective use. Governor Matawalle warned that his administration will not tolerate any abuse of government property and reiterated his administration’s resolve to continue to give priority to the health care delivery sector with special attention to free medical care to women and children. The governor also used the visit to commiserate with patients receiving treatment in the hospital and donated N20,000 to the patients to settle their bills. 